zes the introduction of a 9a-hydroxyl moiety into 1,4-androstadiene-3,17-dione (ADD) to yield the 9alpha-hydroxy-1,4-androstadiene-3,17-dione (9OHADD) intermediate which spontaneously form 3-hydroxy-9,10-seconandrost-1,3,5(10)-triene-9,17-dione (HSA) via the meta-cleavage of ring B with concomitant aromatization of ring A. KSH is also able to use 4-androstene-3,17-dione (AD), 3-oxo-23,24-bisnorcholesta-4-en-22-oate (4-BNC), 3-oxo-23,24-bisnorcholesta-1,4-dien-22-oate (1,4-BNC), 3-oxo-23,24-bisnorcholesta-4-en-22-oyl-coenzyme A thioester (4-BNC-CoA) and 3-oxo-23,24-bisnorcholesta-1,4-dien-22-oyl-coenzyme A thioester (1,4-BNC-CoA) as substrates"}],"commentType":"FUNCTION"},{"commentType":"CATALYTIC ACTIVITY","reaction":{"name":"androsta-1,4-diene-3,17-dione + 2 reduced [2Fe-2S]-[ferredoxin] + O2 + 2 H(+) = 9alpha-hydroxyandrosta-1,4-diene-3,17-dione + 2 oxidized [2Fe-2S]-[ferredoxin] + H2O","reactionCrossReferences":[{"database":"Rhea","id":"RHEA:32199"},{"database":"Rhea","id":"RHEA-COMP:10000"},{"database":"Rhea","id":"RHEA-COMP:10001"},{"database":"ChEBI","id":"CHEBI:15377"},{"database":"ChEBI","id":"CHEBI:15378"},{"database":"ChEBI","id":"CHEBI:15379"},{"database":"ChEBI","id":"CHEBI:33737"},{"database":"ChEBI","id":"CHEBI:33738"},{"database":"ChEBI","id":"CHEBI:40799"},{"database":"ChEBI","id":"CHEBI:63641"}],"ecNumber":"1.14.15.30","evidences":[{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000269","source":"PubMed","id":"19234303"},{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000269","source":"PubMed","id":"21987574"}]},"physiologicalReactions":[{"directionType":"left-to-right","reactionCrossReference":{"database":"Rhea","id":"RHEA:32200"},"evidences":[{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000269","source":"PubMed","id":"19234303"},{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000269","source":"PubMed","id":"21987574"}]}]},{"commentType":"CATALYTIC ACTIVITY","reaction":{"name":"androst-4-ene-3,17-dione + NADH + O2 + H(+) = 9alpha-hydroxy-androst-4-ene-3,17-dione + NAD(+) + H2O","reactionCrossReferences":[{"database":"Rhea","id":"RHEA:45968"},{"dat